    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<h2>Caelith Dunivar — Keeper of Foreign Correspondence</h2>\n<p><em>The Yeomanry civic post that reads, classifies, and replies to incoming political communication from outside the republic. Reports to the Senior Auditor, not the Spokesman — the Audit Hall is institutionally insulated from the Council's factional shifts.</em></p>\n<p>Late fifties, lean, gray hair worn short, scholar's black coat. A small brass quill-pin at the collar (twenty years' service). Walks deliberately. Eyes that catalog before they meet yours.</p>\n<h3>Voice</h3>\n<p>Soft, deliberate. Speaks as if every sentence is going on a record. Uses the formal Yeomanry plural in public; switches to \"I\" only in private, with people he has decided to trust.</p>\n<h3>Combat behavior — Phase 1</h3>\n<p><strong>He will not fight the party in Phase 1, even if pressed.</strong> Combat with him would either resolve the campaign in his favor (he is significantly more dangerous than he reads) or cost the party every political asset Phase 2 depends on. If the party turns on him, he disengages with Cunning Action, retreats from the room, and Phase 2 is unrecoverable.</p>\n<p>The statblock exists for two reasons: so the party feels the right danger if they read him with <em>Insight</em> in the right moment, and so the GM can deploy him as a backstop if Phase 2 demands it.</p>\n<h3>Statblock summary (CR 8, PB +4)</h3>\n<p><strong>AC</strong> 17 · <strong>HP</strong> 127 · <strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft.</p>\n<p><strong>STR</strong> 11 (+0) · <strong>DEX</strong> 18 (+4) · <strong>CON</strong> 16 (+3) · <strong>INT</strong> 15 (+2) · <strong>WIS</strong> 14 (+2) · <strong>CHA</strong> 18 (+4)</p>\n<p><strong>Saves:</strong> DEX +8, INT +6, CHA +8.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Deception +12, Insight +6, Investigation +6, Perception +6, Persuasion +8, Sleight of Hand +8, Stealth +8.</p>\n<p><strong>Senses:</strong> Passive Perception 16. <strong>Languages:</strong> None.</p>\n<h3>Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cunning Action (Recharge 5–6).</strong> Bonus action to Dash, Disengage, or Hide.</li>\n<li><strong>Whisper Network.</strong> While in any settlement where he has contacts, gains advantage on Investigation and Persuasion checks to gather information.</li>\n<li><strong>Words Like Knives (1/Turn).</strong> When Caelith succeeds on a Deception or Persuasion check in social combat (2024 rules), he imposes Disadvantage on the target's next Insight or Persuasion check against him.</li>\n<li><strong>Sneak Attack (1/Turn).</strong> +14 (4d6) damage on a weapon attack if he has advantage or an ally is within 5 ft of the target.</li>\n<li><strong>Uncanny Dodge.</strong> Reaction to halve damage from an attack he can see.</li>\n<li><strong>Evasion.</strong> Takes no damage on successful Dex saves, half on a failed save.</li>\n<li><strong>Silver Tongue.</strong> When Caelith rolls below a 10 on a Deception or Persuasion check, he treats it as a 10.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Actions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cutting Words.</strong> One creature within 30 ft must make a DC 16 Wisdom save. On a failed save: 14 (4d6) psychic damage and Frightened of Caelith until the end of its next turn.</li>\n<li><strong>Dagger.</strong> Ranged Attack +8, range 20/60. <em>Hit:</em> 1d4+3 piercing.</li>\n<li><strong>Rapier.</strong> Melee Attack +8, reach 5 ft. <em>Hit:</em> 1d8+4 piercing.</li>\n<li><strong>Sneak Attack (rider).</strong> +14 (4d6) damage on a successful weapon attack with advantage or an ally within 5 ft of the target.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>For full mechanical automation, drag matching weapon and feature items from the dnd5e SRD compendium and attach them to this actor. The shipped JSON keeps actions as text only.</em></p>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p><em>Blooming Rot, Part 2 — Phase 1.</em> See the <strong>Caelith Dunivar</strong> journal for full profile, public/private speech text, and what he will and will not tell the party.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
